A quote is needed for retrofitting an underground discharge line with a tee and a standpipe that would have a compatible fitting to our 
Godwin Pump discharge lines.
When there is a pump failure at the Intermediate Pumping Station we utilize the Godwin (External) Pump to pump leachate in a tanker truck and 
haul the leachate to the leachate lagoon area and unload the leachate. This is very time consuming and sometimes leads to overtime beyond 
regular business hours. The pump and tanker are also parked on the landfill perimeter road closing one lane and possible causing a safety hazard.
The proposal/estimate should be to insert/install a tee inline to include a standpipe. When installed the pump will be able to pump continuously 
(pump is a dri-prime pump) when connected to this standpipe and only require daily preventive maintenance, fuel, etc. 
The pump will also be put in place in the Intermediate Pumping Station area and not blocking one lane on the perimeter road.

Deb,

I spoke with your tech and discussed the following work scope to be included in the aforesaid work order:
1.	 Apply 3-hr rated fire-barrier sealant/caulking (to the pipe penetration on the floor by the leaking fan-coil unit (fcu).  Doing so will contain and prevent condensate water from leaking down into the Gun Range Room. 
2.	Insulate with at least ½-inch thick fiberglass piping insulation (preferred) for chilled water piping and domestic cold water piping which are producing/leaking condensate water into the ceiling.  Such replacement of piping insulation should not exceed fifty (50) linear feet (lf) of piping insulation.  Apply vapor retardant paint over insulation seams and joints to retain vapor tightness of the insulation.  If replacement of piping insulation should exceed 50 lf, please provide us immediately your price quote for replacing the defective piping insulation.
3.	Perform preventive maintenance (PM) on the ventilation unit for the gun range and for the HVAC equipment for the 2nd floor Locker Room area.  The PM work are not limited to the following standard scope as applicable: 
a.	Replace air filters and belts (if needed/applicable) and date stamp the air-filter media frame using a permanent marker.
b.	Perform performance test by checking voltage, current, superheat, subcooling, operating pressures and temperatures, etc.  Provide us list of recommended repairs if any.  We will address deficiencies in another work order.
c.	Clean evaporator coil and condenser coil if necessary.  
d.	Check for proper operation of the condensate-water drain line and clean trap if required.  
e.	I recommend cleaning electrical contacts with electrical contact cleaner.  
f.	Check and tighten electrical connections.
4.	Provide us a couple of proposals to establish air movement for the gun range and for the other rooms in the basement for proper dehumidification and temperature control. Provide labor and material to clean the cooling tower.  Please have ChemTreat Company c/o Jason Kaplow @ 201-481-8612 provide the proper cleaning of the cooling tower as per SOP:  Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)  1. Disinfection chemicals will added to the system 24 hours prior to cleaning. 2. Lockout all components for each tower to be cleaned. Go through the steps of the procedure and safety procedures including lockout/tagout with everyone on the cleaning team, including customer. 3. Use all necessary PPE safety gear including HEPA respirators.  Only confined space trained personal are allowed to clean out tower interiors. 4. Pressure wash all exterior and interior surfaces, including fill. 5. Clean hot water distribution pans if required.  6. Clean mist eliminators being careful not to damage the plastic. 7. Remove all solid debris from sumps, wet vac, and pressure wash. 8. Flush each cell and sump to a drain.   9. Return to service with existing program’s chemicals and biocides.

Provide labor and material to clean the cooling tower and heat exchanger for the service work. Such service work is not limited to the following scope of work:  Standard Operating Procedure  1. Disinfection chemicals will added to the system 24 hours prior to cleaning. 2. Lockout all components for each tower to be cleaned. Go through the steps of the procedure and safety procedures including lockout/tagout with everyone on                     the cleaning team, including customer. 3. Use all necessary PPE safety gear including HEPA respirators.  Only confined space trained personal are allowed to clean out tower interiors. 4. Pressure wash all exterior and interior surfaces, including fill. 5. Clean hot water distribution pans if required.  6. Clean mist eliminators being careful not to damage the plastic. 7. Remove all solid debris from sumps, wet vac, and pressure wash. 8. Flush each cell and sump to a drain.   9. Return to service with existing program’s chemicals and biocides.
